Statement of Dr. Tilman Barth, University of Washington Anthropology Department:
\par The word }{\i\lang1033\langfe1049\langnp1033\insrsid8201588\charrsid8201588 katsuk }{\lang1033\langfe1049\langnp1033\insrsid8201588\charrsid8201588 is very explicit in Hobuhet's native tongue.\~ 
It means "the center" or the core from which all perception radiates.\~ It's the center of the world or of the universe.\~ It's where an aware individual stands.\~ There has never been any doubt in my mind that Charles is aware.\~ 
I can understand his assuming this pseudonym.
\par You've seen those papers he wrote.\~ That one where he compares the Raven myth of his people to the Genesis myth of Western civilization is very disturbing.\~ He has perceived the link between dream and reality -- how we seek to win a place 
in destiny through rebellion, the evil forces we built up only to destroy, the Great Conquests and Great Causes to which we cling long after they've been exposed as empty glitter.\~ Here . . . notice his simile for such lost perceptions:
\par ". . . the fish eyes like gray skimmed milk that stare at you out of things which are alive when they shouldn't be."
\par This is the observation of someone who is capable of great things, as great as any achievements in our Western mythology.
\par }\pard \s15\qc \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\sbauto1\saauto1\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\ipgp1 {\insrsid8201588 * * *
