Fragment of a note left at the Sam's River shelter:
\par Your words perpetuate illusion.\~ You clot my mind with foreign beliefs.\~ My people taught that Man is dependent upon the goodwill of all other animals.\~ You forbade the ritual which taught this.\~ You said we would be punished for such thoughts.\~ 
I ask you who is being punished now?
\par * * *
\par As they picked their way down the remnants of the rockslide and walked openly into the forest, David told himself the helicopter was sure to return.\~ The men in it had seen his handkerchief.\~ Katsuk as much as admitted that.\~ 
What did all his insane talk about ravens have to do with anything real?\~ The men had seen the handkerchief; they would return.
\par David looked over his shoulder at the cliff, saw a thin cloud above it clinging like a piece of lint to the clear-blown sky.
\par The helicopter would return.\~ People would come on foot.
\par David strained to hear the sound of rotors.
